[b]TVO - The Agenda with Steve Paikin, May 06 2011: &quot;Slut Walks&quot; and Modern Feminism[/b]

[u]The Debate: &quot;Slut Walks&quot; and Modern Feminism[/u]

What started as a Toronto protest has become a global protest. It's called the &quot;slut walk.&quot; Are these demonstrations the newest frontier of feminism? 

[u]Guests:[/u]

[b]Susannah Breslin[/b] is a freelance journalist and blogger.

[b]Jaclyn Friedman[/b] is the executive director at Women, Action and the Media. Visit her personal website.

[b]Gail Dines[/b] is a professor of sociology and women's studies at Wheelock College and author of [i]Pornland[/i].

[b]Heather Jarvis[/b] is co-founder of The Slut Walk.

[b]Kate McPherson[/b] is a professor of history and women's studies at York University.

